 version updates**\\n\\nI’m considering that the existing metadata might only include version 0.0-790, not 1376. I need to prepare to add the tested version 1376 to the existing 0.0-790 bucket. The current tests for 0.0-790 seem comparable to the target and likely pass without special setup. I’ll focus on resolving the target artifact with Gradle dependencies to ensure there are no transitive dependencies. Perhaps I could temporarily use the existing 0.0-790 setup with the GVM_TCK_LV set to 0.0-1376 for testing.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_mI8ZCxDpfgqbUBOc7TBYeu2q|fc_0dc7fb724c3e1eb2016a3e5889de248190b789c39f0e146153", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "env GVM_TCK_LV=0.0-1376 ./gradlew -q dependencyInsight --configuration testRuntimeClasspath --dependency org.clojure:google-closure-library-third-party -Pcoordinates=org.clojure:google-closure-library-third-party:0.0-790", "timeout": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 991, "output": 599, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32310, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782470781256, "responseId": "resp_0dc7fb724c3e1eb2016a3e587dcf6081908ee8439232bfc4d9"}}
